{
  "texts": [
    "The duration of fixation is usually variable, however, the longer the fixation, the more visual information is collected and processed.",
    "• Saccades: Rapid, ballistic movements of the eyes that abruptly change the point of fixation.",
    "Because saccadic movements occur at high speed, vision is impaired.",
    "This is why they are not as important in eye-tracking as fixations.",
    "However, they do reveal information about the direction of the user's gaze and the order of fixations and visual attention."
  ]
}